quran[71]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,He (the Prophet) frowned and turned away
  80,2,"when there came to him the blind man (Ibn Umme Maktum, who came to the Prophet and interrupted his conversation with the chiefs of Mecca)"
  80,3,How could you tell? He might have sought to purify himself
  80,4,or become reminded and might have benefited from Our reminder
  80,5,As for him who is indifferent
  80,6,to whom you were attending
  80,7,you will not be held responsible if he would not purify himself
  80,8,Yet to him who came to you with zeal on his own
  80,9,and with fear of Allah in his heart
  80,10,you gave no heed
  80,11,"It should not be so! Indeed, this is but an admonition"
  80,12,"let him who wants, accept it"
  80,13,"It is written in scrolls, which are honored"
  80,14,"exalted, purified"
  80,15,and which remain in the hands of scribes
  80,16,who are noble and virtuous
  80,17,Woe to man! What a disbeliever he is
  80,18,Out of what Allah has created him
  80,19,Out of a semen-drop! Allah created him and then fashioned him in due proportion
  80,20,then makes his way of life smooth for him
  80,21,then causes him to die and stows him in a grave
  80,22,Then He will surely bring him back to life when He pleases
  80,23,By no means has he fulfilled the duty that Allah had assigned him
  80,24,Let man reflect on the food he eats
  80,25,How We pour down rainwater in abundance
  80,26,and cleave the soil asunder
  80,27,How We bring forth grain
  80,28,grapes and nutritious vegetation
  80,29,olives and dates
  80,30,lush gardens
  80,31,fruits and fodder
  80,32,as a means of sustenance for you and your cattle
  80,33,Finally when there come the deafening blast
  80,34,on that Day each man shall flee from his own brother
  80,35,his mother and his father
  80,36,his wife and his children
  80,37,"For each one of them, on that Day, shall have enough concern of his own to make him indifferent to the others"
  80,38,Some faces on that Day shall be shining
  80,39,smiling and joyful
  80,40,And some faces on that Day shall be dusty
  80,41,and veiled with darkness
  80,42,These shall be the faces of the disbelieving wicked
  81,1,When the sun will cease to shine
  81,2,when the stars will loose their luster
  81,3,when the mountains will be blown away
  81,4,when the ten-month pregnant she-camels will be left unattended
  81,5,when the wild beasts will be brought together
  81,6,when the oceans will be set ablaze
  81,7,when the souls will be reunited with the bodies
  81,8,when the infant girls buried alive (here reference is made to the Pre-Islamic Arab custom of burying new born girls alive) will be questioned
  81,9,for what sin she was killed
  81,10,when the record will be laid open
  81,11,when the heaven will be stripped bare
  81,12,when hell will be set to blaze
  81,13,and when the paradise will be brought near
  81,14,then each soul shall know what it has bought with it
  81,15,But no! I swear by the retreating stars
  81,16,that run their course and hide
  81,17,by the night as it dissipates
  81,18,by the morning when it breaths again
  81,19,surely this word (The Qur’an) is brought by a noble Messenger (Gabriel)
  81,20,"possessor of mighty power, having very high rank with the Owner of the Throne (Allah)"
  81,21,"who is obeyed in heaven, and is trustworthy"
  81,22,O people of Mecca! Your companion has not gone mad
  81,23,he (Muhammad) indeed saw him (Gabriel) in the clear horizon
  81,24,and he is not stingy to withhold the knowledge of the unseen
  81,25,This (Qur’an) is not the word of an accursed Satan
  81,26,Where then are you going
  81,27,This is but a Message to all the people of the world
  81,28,to each one who wishes to follow the Right Way
  81,29,"Yet your wishes are of no avail unless Allah, the Lord of the worlds, pleases so"